Radiographic screening of infants and young children with genetic predisposition 
for rare malignancies: DICER1 mutations and pleuropulmonary blastoma.

Sabapathy DG(1), Guillerman RP, Orth RC, Zhang W, Messinger Y, Foulkes W, Priest 
JR, Annapragada AV.

Author information:
(1)1 Department of Pediatric Radiology, Texas Children's Hospital, 1102 Bates 
Ave, Ste 850, Feigin Center, Houston, TX 77030.

OBJECTIVE: The purpose of this study was to compare the risks of radiation in 
screening strategies using chest radiographs and CT to detect a rare cancer in a 
genetically predisposed population against the risks of undetected disease.
